tgs:Evidence.DiscountMarcus a thinker:Evidence,
        owl:NamedIndividual ;
    thinker:confidence thinker:ConfidenceLevel.Curated ;
    thinker:evidencePolarity thinker:EvidencePolarity.Supports ;
    dct:description "Stoic practice of distinguishing what is/isn't in one's control, and valuing present right action over deferred/imagined future reward, is a philosophical antecedent (not a cited influence) to the behavioral-economics critique of present bias Hagens draws on."@en .

tgs:Evidence.EnergyblindnessBuddha a thinker:Evidence,
        owl:NamedIndividual ;
    thinker:confidence thinker:ConfidenceLevel.Candidate ;
    thinker:evidencePolarity thinker:EvidencePolarity.Supports ;
    dct:description "LLM-suggested: both concern a kind of collective unawareness of the true conditions shaping suffering/behavior (avidya / ignorance vs. energy blindness). Flagged as speculative — needs review before treating as a real link; risk of forcing a surface parallel."@en .

tgs:Evidence.LocalismOstrom a thinker:Evidence,
        owl:NamedIndividual ;
    thinker:confidence thinker:ConfidenceLevel.Curated ;
    thinker:evidencePolarity thinker:EvidencePolarity.Supports ;
    dct:description "Ostrom's Nobel-winning research on communities self-governing shared resources without top-down control or privatization provides the empirical/theoretical backbone for why small-scale local resilience can actually work, rather than just being a romantic ideal."@en .

tgs:Evidence.MetacrisisBateson a thinker:Evidence,
        owl:NamedIndividual ;
    thinker:confidence thinker:ConfidenceLevel.Curated ;
    thinker:evidencePolarity thinker:EvidencePolarity.Supports ;
    dct:description "Bateson's systems-theoretic argument that fragmented, siloed problem-solving itself generates crises ('the pathologies of epistemology') is a direct intellectual ancestor of metacrisis framing used by Hagens and adjacent thinkers."@en .

tgs:Evidence.MlkGrowth a thinker:Evidence,
        owl:NamedIndividual ;
    thinker:confidence thinker:ConfidenceLevel.Curated ;
    thinker:evidencePolarity thinker:EvidencePolarity.Supports ;
    dct:description "MLK's later writing (e.g. his critique of a society organized around 'thing-oriented' rather than 'person-oriented' values, and his turn toward economic justice/the Poor People's Campaign) is a real-world example of confronting a growth/extraction-oriented system, not primarily an ecological argument but a structurally adjacent one worth surfacing as contrast."@en .

tgs:Evidence.OvershootCatton a thinker:Evidence,
        owl:NamedIndividual ;
    thinker:confidence thinker:ConfidenceLevel.Curated ;
    thinker:evidencePolarity thinker:EvidencePolarity.Supports ;
    dct:description "Catton's 1980 book 'Overshoot' coined the term Hagens uses directly; this is a citable lineage, not just a thematic echo."@en ;
    prov:generatedAtTime "1980"^^xsd:gYear .

tgs:Evidence.SuperorganismWilson a thinker:Evidence,
        owl:NamedIndividual ;
    thinker:confidence thinker:ConfidenceLevel.Curated ;
    thinker:evidencePolarity thinker:EvidencePolarity.Supports ;
    dct:description "Wilson's work on eusociality and superorganisms in insect colonies is the direct biological source of the term Hagens applies (with qualification) to human civilization."@en .

tgs:Evidence.WetwareFreud a thinker:Evidence,
        owl:NamedIndividual ;
    thinker:confidence thinker:ConfidenceLevel.Curated ;
    thinker:evidencePolarity thinker:EvidencePolarity.Supports ;
    dct:description "Freud's model of unconscious drives overriding rational self-interest anticipates Hagens' claim that evolved sub-conscious wiring, not conscious reasoning, drives collectively destructive behavior. Different mechanism (psychosexual drives vs. evolutionary mismatch) but the same basic move: rational-actor models are wrong about what's driving behavior."@en .

tgs:Person.MartinLutherKingJr thinker:appliesTo tgs:Concept.GrowthImperative .

